Cemex SAB de CV (CX) Getting Favorable News Coverage, Report Finds

Roana De Caro |
Sábado, Julio 15, 2017







This company shares are 2.34% off its target price of $10.5 and the current market capitalization stands at $15.13B. Three investment analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, seven have assigned a buy rating and four have assigned a strong buy rating to the stock.About Cemex S.A.B.de C.V.
The stock is now moving with a Positive distance from 200-Day Simple Moving Average of about 21.99% and has a pretty decent Year to Date (YTD) Performance of 32.88% which means the stock is constantly adding to its value from previous fiscal year end price. Baillie Gifford & Co. now owns 30,809,554 shares of the construction company's stock valued at $247,400,000 after buying an additional 4,525,660 shares during the period.04/27/2016 - Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Citigroup.Shares of Cemex S.A.B.de C.V.03/18/2016 - Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Jefferies. The current consensus recommendation provided by covering analysts is 2.10.Cemex S.A.B. De C.V. Sponsored (NYSE:CX) now has a trailing P/E of 144.51 while its forward P/E according to Thomson Reuters is 15.31.At the end of 3/31/2017 reporting period, 136 institutional holders increased their position in CEMEX, S.A.B.de C.V. (NYSE:CX) by some 78,537,740 shares, 121 decreased positions by 60,172,475 and 62 held positions by 432,725,757.Yet another important factor while evaluating a good buy/sell decision for CEMEX, S.A.B.de C.V. (CX) is its Earnings per Share or EPS. Morgan Stanley boosted Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. from an "equal weight" recommendation to an "overweight" recommendation and boosted their PT for the shares from $8.50 to $11.00 in a study report on early Tue, Apr 4th.The following firms have also recently changed their position in CX. Commerzbank Aktiengesellschaft FI increased its position in Cemex S.A.B.de C.V.by 48.5% in the Q4. Zacks Investment Research upgraded Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. from a "hold" rating to a "strong-buy" rating and set a $11.00 price target for the company in a research note on Thursday, April 6th. The average 12 month price target among brokers that have updated their coverage on the stock in the a year ago is $10.95. Company chares are trading at $10.26 a tad higher than the 50 day moving average of $8.85 and which is marginally higher than the 200 day moving average of $8.53. (NYSE:CX) last issued its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th.Quarterly Revenue growth year over year is 9.3 Percent. Next quarter's EPS is expected be $0.21 and the next full year EPS is anticipated to be $0.67. BidaskClub upgraded Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. from a "hold" rating to a "buy" rating in a research report on Thursday, June 15th.FMR raised its stake in stocks of Cemex S.A.B.de C.V. (NYSE:CX) by 5.7% during the Q1, based on the latest 13F document with the Security and Exchange Commission. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own 38.83% of the company's stock. Pinnacle Associates purchased a fresh position in stocks of Cemex S.A.B.de C.V.in Q4 which is worth at about $283,000.If you are viewing this piece of content on another site, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of US and global copyright and trademark legislation. If you are viewing this story on another website, it was stolen and reposted in violation of global trademark & copyright laws. The original version of this article can be read at https://transcriptdaily.com/2017/07/13/cemex-s-a-b-de-c-v-cx-upgraded-at-bank-of-america-corporation-updated-updated.html.CEMEX, S.A.B.de C.V. (CEMEX) is an operating and holding company engaged, directly or indirectly, through its operating subsidiaries, primarily in the production, distribution, marketing and sale of cement, ready-mix concrete, aggregates, clinker and other construction materials throughout the world, and that provides construction-related services to customers and communities in over 50 countries throughout the world.




